WEBVTT

00:22.600 --> 00:24.329
<i>(LET ME TAKE OVER PLAYING)</i>

01:32.480 --> 01:34.482
(HORNS HONKING)

01:36.200 --> 01:39.409
Buy 12 at market, unload four at 90,
dump the rest on Friday.

01:39.640 --> 01:42.007
Now don't burn me, Albert.
I'm on the line here.

01:42.120 --> 01:43.963
Ten is break-even. I say 12.

01:44.520 --> 01:46.841
Right. Nothing's impossible, Albert.

01:46.960 --> 01:49.201
Impossible just takes
a couple extra phone calls.

01:50.000 --> 01:52.606
- We're standing still here, Eliot.
-Yes, Mr. Ireland.

01:52.720 --> 01:53.881
I don't like to stand still.

02:12.760 --> 02:17.004
Anne, let me tell you what I need,
flawless clarity, F-color or better.

02:17.080 --> 02:18.491
Fifteen, 20 carats.

02:18.560 --> 02:20.722
Just what you'd want
if I were buying it for you.

02:20.880 --> 02:23.326
Well, I'm rather fussy.

02:28.880 --> 02:29.961
DOUG: Cute.

02:30.400 --> 02:32.243
A little young.
Will you show me their parents?

02:38.000 --> 02:39.206
Nice.

03:27.920 --> 03:30.241
- Morning, Mr. Ireland.
-Morning, Charlie.

03:35.000 --> 03:36.764
- MAN: Hello, Mr. Ireland.
-Hey.

03:37.640 --> 03:39.881
- Good morning, Mr. Ireland.
-Good morning, Nora.

03:40.040 --> 03:41.849
- Good morning.
-Morning.

03:43.480 --> 03:44.891
Nice to see you, Mr. Ireland.

03:44.960 --> 03:46.962
I won't need that giraffe
for about a half an hour.

03:47.080 --> 03:48.684
- Take it out for a walk.
-Very good, sir.

03:49.080 --> 03:50.320
(SNAPS FINGERS)

04:03.440 --> 04:07.126
- Gloria, they're for you. I hope you like them.
-(GASPS)

04:07.240 --> 04:09.049
Oh.

04:09.480 --> 04:10.686
They're beautiful.

04:12.160 --> 04:14.322
- Thank you so much.
-You like them, babe?

04:14.440 --> 04:17.808
You're a doll. You're a great big Iovable doll.

04:17.880 --> 04:18.961
GENE: Yeah? Yeah.

04:19.040 --> 04:21.361
- Mr. Salvatore has exquisite taste.
-GENE: Huh?

04:21.440 --> 04:23.602
Oh, oh. Thank you, uh, Dougie. Here you go.

04:23.680 --> 04:26.604
Listen, it rained all weekend,
so make sure you give them a good workout.

04:26.680 --> 04:30.401
(STAMMERS) I'll take care of it myself, sir.
I have a way with animals.

04:30.480 --> 04:33.450
Dougie, are you the guy
to talk to about them things?

04:34.200 --> 04:36.043
Them things, Mr. Salvatore?

04:36.280 --> 04:39.409
- Yeah, you know. Them things on the pillow.
-Uh,haH?

04:39.480 --> 04:40.606
GLORIA: Genie, get some more
of them things!

04:40.680 --> 04:41.681
Yeah, all right!

04:42.400 --> 04:43.970
You know, them things on the pillow.

04:45.440 --> 04:46.487
Initials.

04:47.520 --> 04:49.841
Them things at night!

04:50.720 --> 04:51.846
On the pillow!

04:53.720 --> 04:56.087
- Mints! Pillow mints!
-Yeah! Yeah!

04:56.160 --> 05:00.131
- Them things. We like them.
-Yes, of course. Why didn't I think?

05:00.200 --> 05:02.202
Stupid. Yes. How many would you like?

05:02.320 --> 05:04.004
- How many? A lot.
-GLORIA: A lot!

05:04.080 --> 05:05.650
A lot, it shall be.

05:05.880 --> 05:08.565
- You're a beautiful kid.
-Enjoy your stay at the Bradbury.

05:10.160 --> 05:12.128
- You're a doll.
-You're a doll.

05:18.800 --> 05:20.370
No, you're a doll.

05:21.080 --> 05:24.289
- Easy, easy. Yo, yip. Come.
-(BARKING)

05:24.920 --> 05:28.561
- Make sure they make!
-Right. Make.

05:29.280 --> 05:30.281
(DOUG GRUNTS)

05:32.600 --> 05:36.491
So, you guys planning
on seeing any shows while you're in town?

05:36.600 --> 05:38.011
-(WHINING)
-(BARKING)

05:38.080 --> 05:39.764
AII right. Okay.

05:45.520 --> 05:47.921
This is Steak Diane.
You guys don't eat this, I will.

05:49.720 --> 05:53.884
You eat all that up, you can have
some of them things when you're done.

05:54.680 --> 05:57.445
- Come on, man. I'm open, I'm open.
-Pass! There it is!

05:57.520 --> 05:59.363
Jump! Score! Yes, yes!

05:59.440 --> 06:00.487
Whoo!

06:00.560 --> 06:03.803
- Carmen, Carmen. Ambulate the canines.
-What?

06:03.960 --> 06:07.123
- Take the dogs for a walk.
-Oh, of course, Mr. Ireland.

06:09.360 --> 06:10.566
(SIGHS)

06:13.920 --> 06:15.570
Ten dollars, Mr. Ireland?

06:15.640 --> 06:19.850
Funny, I, uh, thought this was the Bradbury,
but it must be Fat Harry's Motor Lodge.

06:20.120 --> 06:22.726
Carmen, one day,
you're gonna be a great concierge.

06:22.880 --> 06:26.805
In the meantime,
go get the biggest plastic bag you can find.

06:26.880 --> 06:28.882
- And don't make fun of her hair.
-(WHINES)

06:41.440 --> 06:44.011
Those things aren't candy, Douglas.

06:44.120 --> 06:45.246
I'm not gonna eat them all, ma'am.

06:45.320 --> 06:47.209
Can I get change for that?
I'm in kind of a hurry.

06:47.680 --> 06:49.125
Now let's see.

06:49.320 --> 06:52.130
58 cents out of $100.

06:52.200 --> 06:53.486
It's $99.42.

06:53.600 --> 06:56.570
A whiz kid. Let's just be sure.

06:56.680 --> 07:00.287
- Could you just...
-Uh, $99.42.

07:00.560 --> 07:01.641
Does that look right to you?

07:01.720 --> 07:04.451
You know, anywhere in that ballpark
is gonna be fine.

07:04.520 --> 07:05.760
I'm not fussy.

07:05.840 --> 07:07.444
$19.42.

07:07.520 --> 07:08.726
$99.42.

07:08.920 --> 07:09.921
(CHUCKLES)

07:10.000 --> 07:12.241
You know why I said $19.42?

07:12.760 --> 07:14.762
(LAUGHS) You were trying to cheat me
out of 80 bucks.

07:15.200 --> 07:19.250
(LAUGHS) Iwas married in 1942.

07:19.320 --> 07:21.288
You know, I read that in the Iibrary.

07:21.800 --> 07:23.689
-(LAUGHING)
-(REGISTER RINGS)

07:24.560 --> 07:26.403
I was a war bride.

07:27.160 --> 07:30.528
- Those were horrible, frightening days.
-The war.

07:30.720 --> 07:32.882
No, living with Mr. Vigusian.

07:34.520 --> 07:35.726
-(COINS CLATTERING)
-(EXCLAIMS)

07:36.360 --> 07:37.691
- Just a minute.
-(GROANS)

07:37.840 --> 07:41.686
Yes, if he hadn't fallen
off the Staten Island ferry,

07:42.040 --> 07:45.567
Irving and I would now be married 50 years.

07:45.800 --> 07:51.250
I said, "Irving, get away from the rail!"

07:53.040 --> 07:54.041
Dougie?

07:54.240 --> 07:56.481
Airport?
Take the 59th Street Bridge definitely.

07:57.160 --> 07:59.083
Look, Ahmed, I'm rather skeptical.

07:59.160 --> 08:00.924
It's just that the last belly dancer you sent me

08:01.040 --> 08:02.724
wasn't quite as slender
as I would have hoped.

08:03.640 --> 08:07.486
No, the word "belly" could have applied
to any part of her anatomy.

08:08.160 --> 08:09.650
It's not possible.

08:09.720 --> 08:11.882
DOUG: Ahmed. Ahmed, you're shrieking.

08:12.560 --> 08:13.686
(MUMBLING)

08:14.440 --> 08:17.046
I have an open mind, Ahmed.
It's just that a dancer should have legs.

08:17.120 --> 08:18.724
Doug! Doug!

08:18.800 --> 08:19.801
(WHISPERING) Do something!

08:25.040 --> 08:27.520
Okay, Ahmed, I'II tell you what.
Bottom line here.

08:27.600 --> 08:29.967
You don't start treating me right,
I'm taking my business to Gemal.

08:30.120 --> 08:32.566
Yeah, I'm aware of the blood feud, Ahmed.
I don't care.

08:32.799 --> 08:33.926
<i>Assalam-alaikum.</i>

08:34.000 --> 08:35.001
Milton.

08:36.919 --> 08:39.207
Milton, the Ringos have been
in their room for an hour.

08:39.280 --> 08:40.441
We want it done right.

08:40.520 --> 08:42.203
I keep telling you, two trips if you have to.

08:42.280 --> 08:45.011
These people do not have the time
to wait for you to build the pyramids.

08:45.120 --> 08:49.125
Milton Glickman has never
made two trips in his life and never will.

08:49.360 --> 08:54.127
The Duchess of Windsor, 1948,
41 pieces, one trip.

08:54.280 --> 08:57.045
John Barrymore, 1941,

08:57.120 --> 08:59.361
38 pieces including Mr. Barrymore...

08:59.440 --> 09:01.807
BOTH: Drunk as a lord, one trip.

09:01.960 --> 09:03.962
The Who, 1975...

09:04.040 --> 09:06.202
Just get the bags to the room
before they check out.

09:06.280 --> 09:10.080
167 pieces. One trip.

09:10.520 --> 09:12.807
I spoke to the union. You were wrong.

09:12.880 --> 09:15.724
I am allowed to fire that senile old idiot.

09:15.800 --> 09:17.643
Really? I didn't...

09:17.720 --> 09:20.087
Did you speak to Miss Tantorelli
at the Brooklyn office because...

09:20.160 --> 09:22.401
I want him out.

09:22.480 --> 09:26.007
Look, Mr. Himmelman, you can't fire Milton.
He's been here forever.

09:26.080 --> 09:29.004
A hotel is more
than just facilities and amenities. It's...

09:29.080 --> 09:31.367
Are you trying to tell me how to run a hotel?

09:31.440 --> 09:33.966
No, sir. No, nein. Iwould never do that.

09:34.360 --> 09:36.681
I'm just saying
that the Bradbury's like a family.

09:36.760 --> 09:41.209
It's a place where you have an eccentric
old bellhop or a hotel manager that charges

09:41.280 --> 09:44.648
thousands of dollars in personal
long-distance phone calls to the hotel.

09:44.960 --> 09:48.965
Doesn't mean we want
that family member fired or in jail.

09:50.080 --> 09:51.764
Because that would be
upsetting to the family.

09:51.840 --> 09:52.841
You understand what I'm saying?

09:53.520 --> 09:55.841
Yes, you might be right, Doug.

09:56.000 --> 09:57.206
Happens.

10:03.000 --> 10:06.971
Hey, Vincent, what's happening
in your sordid little world today?

10:07.040 --> 10:08.121
Divorce court.

10:08.200 --> 10:09.804
WOMAN: ...to the most fabulous city
in the world

10:09.920 --> 10:11.331
and your idea of a second honeymoon

10:11.400 --> 10:14.085
is sitting in a dark room,
drinking a Diet Pepsi

10:14.160 --> 10:15.764
and eating a tuna fish sandwich.

10:15.840 --> 10:16.966
MAN: I'm just about ready to go, honey.

10:17.040 --> 10:19.964
Where? Back to the room
to watch Wheel of Fortune?

10:20.040 --> 10:21.405
I came here to fall in love again.

10:21.480 --> 10:23.164
AIl you want to do is fall asleep.

10:36.600 --> 10:37.840
It was a very good sandwich. Thank you.

10:40.240 --> 10:43.210
He's doomed, Dougie.
The rube's marriage is doomed.

10:43.280 --> 10:44.327
<i>YeP-</i>

10:44.400 --> 10:45.925
Them hicks have difficulties,

10:46.040 --> 10:49.044
when to plant things,
which shirt to put on the scarecrow,

10:49.120 --> 10:50.167
pressure builds up.

10:50.240 --> 10:52.163
Well, there's nothing we can do about it.

10:52.240 --> 10:56.040
"We?" Dougie, I'm just a bartender.
You're the concierge.

10:57.240 --> 10:59.242
Hey, he seemed like a nice guy.

10:59.520 --> 11:01.887
Yeah, well, that nice guy
left you a half a buck tip.

11:03.240 --> 11:04.730
You save his marriage.

11:04.800 --> 11:08.009
VINCENT: Dougie! You kept me
and the missus out of divorce court!

11:08.080 --> 11:09.764
DOUG: Yeah, yeah, yeah.

11:20.960 --> 11:22.724
MAN: $16 for tuna fish?

11:22.800 --> 11:24.928
WOMAN: Harry, will you stop talking
about tuna fish?

11:25.000 --> 11:27.890
- MAN: Not when it costs more than my shoes.
-There you are, sir.

11:28.880 --> 11:31.360
- I have those tickets for you.
-Tickets?

11:31.640 --> 11:33.130
The tickets you called about.

11:33.200 --> 11:35.521
Now I could only get fourth-row orchestra.
I'm sorry.

11:35.600 --> 11:38.080
Miss Saigon is very tough
to get at the last second.

11:38.160 --> 11:41.209
Also I made reservations for a late dinner
at the Rainbow Room.

11:41.280 --> 11:43.282
My friend Gigi,
the maitre d', is expecting you.

11:43.440 --> 11:47.081
And as per instructions,
the hotel limo will pick you up at the theater.

11:47.960 --> 11:51.487
Why, Sparky, you really had me going.

11:52.280 --> 11:55.602
Oh, my God. I can't go to the Rainbow Room
with my hair like this.

11:57.200 --> 11:59.441
Ask for Kenneth. He does Ivana.

11:59.600 --> 12:00.886
Thank you.

12:07.680 --> 12:09.409
Well, you came through like a pro.

12:09.480 --> 12:11.005
How'd you know?

12:11.080 --> 12:13.048
I'm the concierge. I know everything.

12:13.680 --> 12:15.045
You do yourjob very well.

12:15.120 --> 12:17.691
She hasn't called me "Sparky"
in a real long time.

12:18.720 --> 12:21.769
Look, I don't know
exactly how to do this, but...

12:24.000 --> 12:27.482
Uh, look, don't confuse yourself
with all these little denominations.

12:27.840 --> 12:30.605
You wait until
I'm the best friend you ever had.

12:30.680 --> 12:32.250
Then you give me a tip so big,

12:32.600 --> 12:34.841
it feels like passing a kidney stone.

12:35.600 --> 12:37.045
OW. That bad, huh?

12:37.120 --> 12:38.246
If I'm worth it.

12:38.360 --> 12:40.840
-(PHONE RINGING)
-Excuse me, Sparky.

12:43.120 --> 12:44.360
(RINGING CONTINUES)

12:44.440 --> 12:45.646
Concierge.

12:45.760 --> 12:48.445
<i>Dougie, it's Jeanette Vigusian.</i>

12:48.520 --> 12:49.567
Yes, Mrs. Vigusian?

12:50.000 --> 12:51.604
<i>From the newsstand?</i>

12:51.680 --> 12:53.284
Yes, I know, Mrs. Vigusian.

12:53.360 --> 12:54.486
<i>Have you got a minute?</i>

12:54.560 --> 12:55.686
Uh, no, I don't.

12:55.760 --> 12:58.604
<i>You don't have a minute?</i>

12:58.680 --> 13:00.205
Yes, Mrs. Vigusian. I have a minute.

13:00.680 --> 13:03.331
I thought so. Everybody has a minute.

13:03.480 --> 13:04.561
Uh, Mrs. Vigusian...

13:04.640 --> 13:07.007
What about settling down, Dougie?

13:07.120 --> 13:08.963
Marriage, children...

13:09.040 --> 13:11.281
<i>Okay, l will. Thanks, Mrs. Vigusian.</i>

13:11.360 --> 13:12.646
Over there by the fem.

13:12.720 --> 13:14.085
Settle down over there by the fern.

13:14.160 --> 13:17.562
<i>With her, over there by the fern.</i>

13:18.400 --> 13:21.131
Oh, good idea, Mrs. Vigusian. I'll marry her.

13:21.320 --> 13:22.560
<i>- Good.
- Thanks.</i>

13:25.560 --> 13:26.891
(EXHALES)

13:32.240 --> 13:34.527
Some sweet? No?

13:43.840 --> 13:44.966
Check this out.

13:45.800 --> 13:47.290
That's the new Julian Russell girl.

13:47.360 --> 13:49.488
Hottest designer, hottest model.

13:49.560 --> 13:52.040
Not many guys have their fantasies
come true, Doug,

13:52.120 --> 13:53.884
but today I get mine.

13:53.960 --> 13:56.645
Great. Look, you know
how risky this is, right?

13:56.720 --> 13:57.801
I could get fired.

13:57.880 --> 13:59.609
I really owe you.

13:59.680 --> 14:01.444
And I'm really gonna collect.

14:02.160 --> 14:03.207
You speak to your boss yet?

14:03.320 --> 14:04.685
Sure, sure.
He says he wants to meet with you.

14:04.760 --> 14:06.603
You showed him the proposal?
He was interested?

14:06.680 --> 14:07.841
Hey, the guy gets 50 proposals a week.

14:07.920 --> 14:11.003
He's not gonna write a blank check just
because some bellhop thinks he has an idea.

14:11.120 --> 14:12.565
I'm not a bellhop, okay. I'm a concierge.

14:12.640 --> 14:15.849
Relax. Four years ago,
Hanover found Julian Russell and he...

14:15.920 --> 14:18.082
Schlepping suits
in the Garment District for 75 bucks.

14:18.160 --> 14:20.162
Now Julian Russell
is the fourth small business

14:20.240 --> 14:22.004
Hanover's turned to gold since 1985.

14:22.080 --> 14:23.445
Hey, good boy. You did your homework.

14:23.520 --> 14:24.726
Yeah, well, I...

14:28.800 --> 14:29.881
Now you be a good boy.

14:29.960 --> 14:31.371
I need that room back by 2:00.

14:31.440 --> 14:32.771
No problem.

14:33.000 --> 14:34.570
(DOUG CLEARS THROAT)

14:38.720 --> 14:39.721
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

14:39.800 --> 14:42.371
Hey, Doug, look, uh, Iforgot something.

14:42.440 --> 14:45.364
I was supposed to pick up
some package at Barney's for Mr. Hanover.

14:45.440 --> 14:47.920
- It's a present for his wife.
-Jesus Christ.

14:48.000 --> 14:50.606
Come on, Doug.
This could be your last day as a bellhop.

14:51.160 --> 14:52.685
Concierge.

14:55.400 --> 14:57.164
(SNIFFS)

14:58.040 --> 15:01.249
I can't tell a thing.
It's all confused with the other scents.

15:01.720 --> 15:02.926
Perhaps on your wrist.

15:03.000 --> 15:05.321
Perhaps not. Lend me an ear.

15:05.520 --> 15:06.851
What?

15:09.320 --> 15:10.970
(SNIFFING)

15:13.040 --> 15:14.451
Too woodsy.

15:15.320 --> 15:16.924
Would you like a second opinion?

15:17.600 --> 15:18.601
Could you?

15:18.680 --> 15:20.284
Sure. Miss?

15:24.960 --> 15:27.122
(SNIFFING DEEPLY)

15:27.200 --> 15:28.850
-(LAUGHING)
-(SNORTING)

15:29.240 --> 15:30.401
You're absolutely right.

15:30.480 --> 15:32.801
You might as well
glue a little pinecone back there.

15:32.880 --> 15:34.450
Oh, woodsy, I'm not.

15:34.520 --> 15:36.443
No, no. Top of my head, I would say

15:36.520 --> 15:38.807
that you were, uh...

15:38.880 --> 15:41.565
Ah, miss,
a bottle of Joy de Jean Patou, please.

15:41.680 --> 15:44.411
My girlfriend wears this.
Now she's about your age.

15:44.600 --> 15:48.924
Well, actually, she's not your age. She'Il be
38 in June and you're probably, what, 34?

15:49.520 --> 15:53.161
Anyway, Joy is what she wears,
and I got to tell you.

15:53.240 --> 15:55.686
- That heady musk...
-(INHALES DEEPLY)

15:55.760 --> 15:57.603
...spicy experience,

15:59.240 --> 16:01.891
tempered by a sweet innocence

16:02.080 --> 16:06.483
has this boy rooting and foraging
morning, noon and night.

16:09.000 --> 16:11.048
(INHALES AND SIGHS HEAVILY)

16:11.680 --> 16:13.125
You be careful.

16:14.840 --> 16:16.330
She'II help you with that.

16:20.160 --> 16:21.650
(GIGGLES) You are some piece of work.

16:21.720 --> 16:23.484
Hey, I got her out of your face, didn't I?

16:23.560 --> 16:25.005
"Rooting and foraging"?

16:25.080 --> 16:28.050
Tell people what they want to hear,
you can sell 'em anything.

16:28.120 --> 16:29.326
What a lovely thought.

16:29.400 --> 16:31.482
Now here's a lovely thought,
you, me, Friday night.

16:31.560 --> 16:33.881
- Miss Saigon, fourth row, on the aisle.
-Doug, don't start.

16:33.960 --> 16:34.961
Cowboy Junkies at the Ritz.

16:35.040 --> 16:37.122
- I'm not going through this again.
-Monster trucks at the Garden.

16:37.200 --> 16:38.406
<i>Sesame Street on Ice.</i>

16:38.640 --> 16:40.085
I've got a boyfriend.

16:40.160 --> 16:42.845
You know,
you've used that excuse a number of times.

16:42.920 --> 16:45.207
Well, it's handy, and it's true.

16:45.280 --> 16:47.408
I hope this guy treats you okay.

16:47.840 --> 16:49.365
VVhy?

16:49.440 --> 16:50.771
Does he?

16:51.200 --> 16:52.565
On and off.

16:52.640 --> 16:53.687
Lately?

16:53.760 --> 16:55.569
We spent last weekend in Saint Barts.

16:55.640 --> 16:57.608
You don't look very tanned.
You get rained out?

16:58.600 --> 17:01.126
"No, Doug, we just never
made it out of the room."

17:01.600 --> 17:03.011
AII right, I'll tell you what,
I'm gonna come back

17:03.080 --> 17:04.366
when I'm older, richer and married.

17:04.440 --> 17:06.124
That way, you won't be able to resist me.

17:06.200 --> 17:07.690
Never said he was married.

17:09.040 --> 17:10.280
Listen, I've got to go.

17:12.880 --> 17:14.119
He's married.

17:18.359 --> 17:19.805
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

17:23.599 --> 17:25.364
Gary, you were supposed to be
out of there an hour ago.

17:25.480 --> 17:27.608
I got newlyweds coming in at 5:00.

17:27.760 --> 17:29.250
Doug, I did it.

17:29.360 --> 17:30.441
Spare me the details.

17:30.520 --> 17:33.729
